[2026-06-13]  DEPENDENCY RECOVERY & REACT 19 MIGRATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Context: `npm audit fix --force` had upgraded Next.js 14 -> 16 while leaving
 React 18 + react-three-fiber v8, crashing the app with
 "Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'ReactCurrentOwner')".

 - Restored package.json / package-lock.json / tsconfig.json from git, then
   performed a clean, intentional upgrade.
 - Migrated the stack to React 19:
     next            14.2.5 -> ^16.2.9
     react           18     -> ^19
     react-dom       18     -> ^19
     @react-three/fiber  8  -> ^9.0.0   (fixes the ReactCurrentOwner crash)
     @react-three/drei   9  -> ^10.0.0
     next-themes     0.3    -> ^0.4.6
     nodemailer      7      -> ^8.0.11  (fixes SMTP-injection advisory)
     @types/react / @types/react-dom  18 -> ^19
 - npm vulnerabilities: 91 -> 2 (the 2 remaining are postcss bundled inside
   Next 16 itself; build-time only, not fixable without Next changing its dep).
 - Verified: `tsc --noEmit` clean, `next build` clean, dev boots (HTTP 200),
   and the 3D Hero scene renders in a real WebGL context with ZERO
   ReactCurrentOwner errors (verified by driving headless Chrome via CDP).

